JOHANNESBURG - The DA wants parliament to provide protection for members of a committee probing corruption at SOEs, including Eskom. It says witnesses who have given damning evidence should also be protected. WATCH: Minister Brown testifies at Parliamentary inquiry on Eskom The opposition says its member on the committee, Natasha Mazzone, has been recently followed by unknown cars and her vehicle was tampered with. Two weeks ago the inquiry's evidence leader Advocate Ntuthuzelo Vanara claimed State Security Minister Bongani Bongo tried to bribe him. eNCA